UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Randy WILLIAMS, also known as Randy Lafitte, Defendant-Appellant. No. 08-30581

Conference Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Feb. 18, 2009. Mary J. Mudrick, U.S. Attorney’s Office Western District of Louisiana, Shreveport, LA, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Randy Lafitte, Betty Lee Marak, Federal Public Defender’s Office Western District of Louisiana Shreveport, LA, for Defendant-Appellant. *690Before HIGGINBOTHAM, DENNIS, and PRADO, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

The Federal Public Defender appointed to represent Randy Williams has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Williams has not filed a response. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Che R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
